Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Zest and quarter
@lemon{1} (for 4 servings, zest one lemon and quarter both). Mince
@chives{1/4%oz}(minced) (all for 4).

== Lemony Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups water
for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

While rice cooks, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of
@cooking oil{2%tsp}, salt, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Carefully toss with half the lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice.

== Creamy Chive Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over
with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}
over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat same pan over medium-high heat. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1},
half the @Dijon mustard{2%tsp} (all for 4 servings), ¼ cup water (1/3 cup for 4),
and a squeeze of lemon juice. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Turn off heat.

Stir in @sour cream{2%tbsp} and minced chives.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, add more water 1 tsp at a time until it reaches
> a drizzling consistency.

Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and
remaining lemon zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide chicken, rice, and broccoli between plates. Drizzle chicken with pan sauce.
Cut remaining lemon into wedges and serve on the side.